[3] Arkansas (Washington County)
Date: Mon 2 Dec 2019 2:50 PM CST
Source: Northwest Arkansas Democrat Gazette [abridged, edited]
https://www.nwaonline.com/news/2019/dec/02/second-student-at-fayetteville-s-washin/


A 2nd Washington Elementary School student has a confirmed case of pertussis, the School District announced [Mon 2 Dec 2019]. The 1st case of pertussis, or whooping cough, was announced Tuesday [26 Nov 2019?].

The Arkansas Department of Health requires students in the same school with a student who has a confirmed case of pertussis who have an exemption for the pertussis vaccine or no record of the vaccination to be excluded from school for 21 days from the date of exposure.

At least 6 students in the School District have been diagnosed with pertussis since last spring [2019].

[Byline: Dave Perozek]

